# Step sequencer jsui — rules and context

## What it is
- Drift step sequencer for Max: gate toggles, piano-roll pitch grid, per-step octave (-1/0/+1), scale mask, per-step accent.
- TypeScript/ES modules in src/ → single file dist/step_sequencer.js for Max jsui. Spec in SPEC.md.

## Build pipeline (do not break)
1. Esbuild: bundle src/main.ts → IIFE (ES2018).
2. Babel: transpile to ES5 (IE11) — Max’s jsui engine is old (no arrows, etc.).
3. Post-fixes: convert remaining arrows in __esm/__commonJS and .sort().
4. Banner: first line must be `var __maxGlobal = this;` so install() gets the jsui global. Replace install(g) with install(typeof __maxGlobal !== "undefined" ? __maxGlobal : g). Without this, the UI does not draw.

## Max jsui constraints
- Top-level this is the jsui object (mgraphics, outlet). Inside the IIFE, globalThis is not that object — hence __maxGlobal.
- Handlers (paint, onresize, onclick, msg_int, list, etc.) are called by Max; use ctx.call(this) or closed-over global so mgraphics/outlet are correct. For msg_int/list, use invocation context for inlet index (this.inlet or global.inlet).
- ES5 only: no Number.isNaN (use isNaN()), no other ES6+ Number.* or unsupported APIs.
- onclick: Max may pass (x, y, button) or (button, x, y); detect by (a1 in 0–2 and a2 > 50) for (button, x, y). Wrap outlet calls in try/catch (safeOutletCall) so a bad outlet() does not surface as “error calling function onclick”. Wrap full onclick body in try/catch and in catch only use global.mgraphics.redraw() (no ctx.call(this) in catch).
- hitTest: guard against cellW/cellH 0 (safeCol); import MARGIN in hitTest.ts.

## Key source
- main.ts: install(global), assigns paint, onresize, onclick, msg_int, list, setpattern, bang, loadbang; ensureInited, syncSizeFromMgraphics, safeOutletCall for onclick.
- SequencerState.ts: state, layout, outputStep, loadPatternFromArray, handleMsgInt, handleScaleMaskList.
- draw.ts, hitTest.ts, logic.ts, constants.ts, types.ts.

## Commands
- npm run build — produce dist/step_sequencer.js.
- npm run typecheck && npm test && npm run check — validate before commit.
- nvm use — match Node (see .nvmrc).

## Integration
- Point jsui filename at dist/step_sequencer.js (absolute path recommended; Max often does not resolve from search path). See instruments/drift/docs/STEP_SEQUENCER_JSUI.md.
